ce:section.ce:para:
In order to demonstrate the feasibility of the as-proposed method in real samples, tap water and lake water were used as real samples, which were taken from our lab and Hongzi Lake in the campus of our university. After pretreated by qualitative filter paper and 0.22 μm filter membrane to remove the solid suspensions and other impurities, the water samples were spiked with Hg2+ and ziram at various concentrations. Finally, the recovery tests were performed by the as-proposed methods. The recoveries are in the range from 98.92% to 105.17% and 95.36% to 106.83%, for the detection of Hg2+ in tap water and lake water samples (Table 1
                        ), in the range from 102.29% to 106.67% and 99.50% to 109.71% (Table 2
                        ) for the detection of zriam in tap water and lake water samples. Despite the complicated components in the real samples which may interfere with the detections, the spiked Hg2+ and ziram can be recovered with accuracy. It indicates that the proposed methods are of high selectivity.
